  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This phase II study examines the safety and efficacy of combination therapy for hypertension
      in patients with autosomal dominant polycystic kidney disease (ADPKD). This study examines
      the safety and efficacy of combination therapy by imidapril (ACEI) or cilnidipine (CCB) in
      ADPKD patients whose blood pressure is not controlled under 120/80 mmHg by candesartan (ARB)
      alone.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Maximum dosage of candesartan is 8 mg/day. Dosage of imidapril is in the range of 2.5-10
      mg/day. Dosage of cilnidipine is in the range of 5-20mg/day.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
